wiki_section_title: Syrian detainees at Guantanamo

wiki_section_text: 

intro: The United States Department of Defense was holding a total of eleven
Syrian detainees in Guantanamo. A total of 778 suspects have been held in the Guantanamo Bay detention camps, in Cuba since the camps opened on January 11, 2002
The camp population peaked in 2004 at approximately 660.
